      <li id="YiKx">
        <p>New favourite place to think and write</p>
        <ul>
          <li id="ek">
            <p>22 GF Northumberland Street.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Vway">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="kv">
            <p>Sitting in the kitchen, I can look out the window at night. There is a</p>
          </li>
          <li id="oO">
            <p>green streetlight. It is very comforting, as if time has stopped. You</p>
          </li>
          <li id="IA">
            <p>can see it from the bedroom, but I do not wish to lie down.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="e0">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="7m">
            <p>My only problem is that the wifi is limited here. But is that a</p>
          </li>
          <li id="TU3">
            <p>problem? Maybe what I need is no wifi. An ability to disconnect. To</p>
          </li>
          <li id="xGC">
            <p>"re-charge". If I can setup tasks whilst I have a connection, I can</p>
          </li>
          <li id="dt8">
            <p>continue them here.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="WbV">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="bul">
            <p>I think if I lived alone and not with Arina, I would use the bedroom</p>
          </li>
          <li id="f7D">
            <p>as a place for my desk. Sometimes I wonder&amp;#x2026; is that still possible?</p>
          </li>
          <li id="8bx">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="ZlS">
            <p>What if we moved her makeup table into the lounge? It is probably too</p>
          </li>
          <li id="ReC">
            <p>exposed there I guess. I suppose she would not like it. And of</p>
          </li>
          <li id="2kV">
            <p>course.. the problem of no connection.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="UAm">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="PEx">
            <p>Not to worry.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="bK7">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="XAk">
            <p>What might be nice is to try and get a lamp and bring it in here. I</p>
          </li>
          <li id="pSh">
            <p>really like the idea of buying that old office lamp from that antique</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Sy7">
            <p>store down the road. I wonder if it is still for sale? This would</p>
          </li>
          <li id="BHW">
            <p>allow me to read. To save money perhaps I could move one of the night</p>
          </li>
          <li id="0C-">
            <p>lights from the bedroom into this room. I wonder&amp;#x2026; where should I</p>
          </li>
          <li id="D94">
            <p>plug it?</p>
          </li>
          <li id="MVa">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="ffD">
            <p>Okay, I found the perfect light. The orange one. However, we'll likely</p>
          </li>
          <li id="hVe">
            <p>have to buy another??? Maybe not, if I put the lamp up on the shelf</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Q74">
            <p>perhaps it will work.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="s-Q">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="TB3">
            <p>There is something so nice about working like this late at night. It's</p>
          </li>
          <li id="D12">
            <p>almost as if I forgot all about it. A calmness, a tranquilitiy. It is</p>
          </li>
          <li id="hr1">
            <p>very liberating.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="INu">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="-FY">
            <p>I have a theory that in order for the internet to work properly, I'll</p>
          </li>
          <li id="92e">
            <p>need to leave the living room door ajar. Isn't it funny how th most</p>
          </li>
          <li id="cm_">
            <p>unlikely of rooms (or thought to be unlikely of rooms) can suddenly</p>
          </li>
          <li id="w6D">
            <p>become so homely and welcoming.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="UqW">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="rWg">
            <p>Perhaps in terms of the wifi, there is some kind of range extender</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Not">
            <p>that I can use. I'm still undecided on it. Does it bring me any</p>
          </li>
          <li id="5pk">
            <p>benefit, or not?</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Fm6J">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="ajE">
            <p>Vincent is funny. Seems to live on my cadence. He's suddenly exploring</p>
          </li>
          <li id="D1L">
            <p>the place after I moved some things around. The more I live with this</p>
          </li>
          <li id="1Iy">
            <p>cat alone, the more I begi to understand him. Him and I are not too</p>
          </li>
          <li id="CJ2">
            <p>unalike.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Hd0">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="0N0">
            <p>I could open the door and make this a legitimate working environment</p>
          </li>
          <li id="6oi">
            <p>(whatever that means). The only thing I'm worried about is that bloody</p>
          </li>
          <li id="O78">
            <p>fly. Maybe I need some fly killer or something. &amp;#x2026; &amp;#x2026; to be fair, I</p>
          </li>
          <li id="hyY">
            <p>haven't tried working from the main room this late at night. Maybe I</p>
          </li>
          <li id="4CA">
            <p>should give it a try&amp;#x2026; will I feel too expose with the screen so bright?</p>
          </li>
          <li id="rUs">
            <p/>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li id="It02">
        <p>SwiftUI Body Composition</p>
        <ul>
          <li id="nwWp">
            <p>The composition of apps with SwiftUI is 1000x easier than I</p>
          </li>
          <li id="qR">
            <p>remember. It should be quite easy to develop apps with greater speed</p>
          </li>
          <li id="97B3">
            <p>now.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="l6">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="Uo">
            <p>And it seems more fun than I remember. The previous constraint system was awful.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="2FXS">
            <p/>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li id="RpY4">
        <p>Music from Kafka on the Shore</p>
        <ul>
          <li id="egwu">
            <p>The Rubinstein, Heifetz and Feuermann trio. Musical references from</p>
          </li>
          <li id="AR">
            <p>[Murakami's](20230709T124613--haruki-murakami.md) [Kafka on the Shore](20230709T124541--kafka-on-the-shore.md).</p>
          </li>
          <li id="4U">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="Hu">
            <p>Archduke trio.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="2Y">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="N_0Y">
            <p>Pierre Fournier.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="RZCy">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="oG">
            <p>Haydn</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li id="9hjF">
        <p/>
      </li>
      <li id="ZmLO">
        <p>Steph Ango on writing todos</p>
        <ul>
          <li id="MbMb">
            <p>I've just tried GTD. I don't like it. It doesn't work. For some reason</p>
          </li>
          <li id="2e">
            <p>my stuff is not synchronised. It pissed me off.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="4lGI">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="Sz">
            <p>I sort of like [Stephan Ango's approach here](https://stephanango.com/todos). Make a list weekly of</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Ha">
            <p>important things to do. The rest will fall away naturally. You can</p>
          </li>
          <li id="7c">
            <p>sort the signal from the noise this way.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="sC">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="pJ">
            <p>Any "habits" should be ingrained to the extent that you don't need to</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Ld">
            <p>write them out.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="bdYm">
            <p/>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li id="gHwC">
        <p>Jonathan Blow on time management</p>
        <ul>
          <li id="jvZl">
            <p>Basically: "[you don't need time management](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3SW7CsUrIy4)".</p>
          </li>
          <li id="KL">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="gg">
            <p>What you want to do is track the time spent *doing the thing*.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="xE">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="Ft">
            <p>This is the real metric. Don't plan you time -&gt; ass in chair</p>
          </li>
          <li id="uq">
            <p>mindset. This roughly maps to [Stephan Ango's practice of weekly to-do</p>
          </li>
          <li id="sS">
            <p>lists](20230716T140306--stephen-ango-on-writing-to-dos.md).</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Mq61">
            <p/>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li id="YrSX">
        <p>Jonathan Blow on burnout and productivity</p>
        <ul>
          <li id="wf-J">
            <p>Interesting talk on burnout, productivity and ambition. [Watch on</p>
          </li>
          <li id="fz">
            <p>YouTube here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zewGodTzZ2Y). It is important to be [mindful about where and when</p>
          </li>
          <li id="vV">
            <p>productivity is important](20230702T162402--new-workflow-weekly.md).</p>
          </li>
          <li id="ZQ">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="hA">
            <p>This relates to his other talk on [getting things done and time management](20230716T140526--jonathan-blow-on-time-management.md).</p>
          </li>
          <li id="xGX_">
            <p/>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li id="h2yd">
        <p>Storing Emacs configuration on iCloud Drive</p>
        <ul>
          <li id="Pc1K">
            <p>Sure, to store your Emacs configuration file (typically a file named</p>
          </li>
          <li id="L8">
            <p>".emacs" or a directory named ".emacs.d") on your iCloud Drive and</p>
          </li>
          <li id="czZC">
            <p>make Emacs use that configuration, you can follow the steps below:</p>
          </li>
          <li id="WJZ4">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="dfis">
            <p>1.  ****Backup your existing Emacs configuration****: Before making any</p>
            <ul>
              <li id="SR">
                <p>changes, make sure to backup your existing Emacs configuration</p>
              </li>
              <li id="pQ">
                <p>files. They are typically located in your home directory \`~\`. The</p>
              </li>
              <li id="dJ">
                <p>primary configuration file is usually named \`.emacs\`, and some</p>
              </li>
              <li id="6z">
                <p>configurations are stored in a directory named \`.emacs.d\`.</p>
              </li>
              <li id="an">
                <p/>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li id="hs">
            <p>2.  ****Move your Emacs configuration to iCloud Drive****: iCloud Drive on</p>
            <ul>
              <li id="xy">
                <p>macOS is typically found at \`~/Library/Mobile</p>
              </li>
              <li id="UB">
                <p>Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs\`. Move your Emacs configuration file</p>
              </li>
              <li id="xC">
                <p>or directory into this directory. If you're using Terminal, you can</p>
              </li>
              <li id="rA">
                <p>use the \`mv\` command to do this. For example:</p>
              </li>
              <li id="MH">
                <p/>
                <ul>
                  <li id="uj">
                    <p>mv ~/.emacs.d ~/Library/Mobile\ Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/</p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="LO">
                    <p/>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li id="oD">
                <p>This moves your Emacs configuration to your iCloud Drive.</p>
              </li>
              <li id="Fs">
                <p/>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li id="-M">
            <p>3.  ****Create symbolic links to the new location****: Emacs will still</p>
            <ul>
              <li id="KW">
                <p>look for your configuration in your home directory, so you need to</p>
              </li>
              <li id="Ja">
                <p>create symbolic links from the original location to the new</p>
              </li>
              <li id="Mg">
                <p>location. You can use the \`ln -s\` command in Terminal to create</p>
              </li>
              <li id="Fp">
                <p>these symbolic links. For example:</p>
              </li>
              <li id="YG">
                <p/>
                <ul>
                  <li id="Z7">
                    <p>ln -s ~/Library/Mobile\ Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/.emacs.d ~/.emacs.d</p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="oX">
                    <p/>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li id="v9">
                <p>This creates symbolic links from your home directory to your Emacs</p>
              </li>
              <li id="sT">
                <p>configuration on iCloud Drive.</p>
              </li>
              <li id="OF">
                <p/>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li id="FF">
            <p>4.  ****Check your setup****: Open Emacs to check that your configuration</p>
            <ul>
              <li id="6H">
                <p>is working correctly. If Emacs opens with your settings, the setup</p>
              </li>
              <li id="bA">
                <p>is successful.</p>
              </li>
              <li id="Mkpq">
                <p/>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li id="dP">
            <p>Remember that changes to files in iCloud Drive are uploaded to iCloud,</p>
          </li>
          <li id="q4tp">
            <p>so you'll need an internet connection for changes to sync. If you make</p>
          </li>
          <li id="DS">
            <p>changes to your Emacs configuration while offline, the changes won't</p>
          </li>
          <li id="QQ">
            <p>sync to iCloud until you're online again.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="sr">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="kx">
            <p>As of my last training data in September 2021, Apple doesn't</p>
          </li>
          <li id="Uj">
            <p>officially support app-specific files (like \`.emacs\` or \`.emacs.d\`) in</p>
          </li>
          <li id="1U">
            <p>iCloud Drive across multiple macOS devices, so your mileage may vary</p>
          </li>
          <li id="jC">
            <p>depending on how iCloud Drive is implemented on your specific devices</p>
          </li>
          <li id="0o11">
            <p>and software versions.</p>
          </li>
          <li id="aE">
            <p/>
          </li>
          <li id="OckJ">
            <p/>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
